            <div >
              <p>Recreational activities are carried out extensively in jails to channelize the inmates
                energy towards positive causes. There is a provision of television set in each barrack. 
                The newspaper, magazines and books are available. There is a provision for sports and 
                cultural activities and inter-jail tournaments are organized. The salient features are as 
                under:</p>
              <ul type="disc">
                <li><p>Television Sets with DTH System, LCDs and PA System are provided in all the 
                  barrack/cells of inmates.</p></li>
                <li><p>Besides this, a music system is also available in the jail in which devotional songs,
                  chants, bhajans are being played in the jail in the morning time and other special 
                  occasions. In addition to this, different musical instruments like tabla, chimta, dholak
                  and harmonium are also provided to inmates in order to inculcate positivity among 
                  them.</p></li>
                <li><p>Indoor games like Volley Ball, Carrom Board, Chess, and Badminton are also played 
                  by the inmates. Volley ball, Badminton, Kabaddi matches are being organised inside 
                  jail.</p></li>
                <li><p>Meditation and Yoga: - Weekly Yoga and Meditation camps are held in side jail with 
                  the help of NGOs i.e. Art of living and international Yoga.</p></li>
                  <li><p>Computer and Electronic type writer are provided in jail.</p></li>
                  <li><p>adequate facilities and medical equipment, equivalent standards and links with public health
                    services for consultations and transitions,
                    	 knowledge of the population-based distribution of risk
                    and disease,
                     a supportive prison culture;</p></li>
                     <li><p>Prisoners were provided medical treatment by mega medical camp by Civil Hospital 
                      and NGO.Legal Aid Clinic has been open with the help of local Court so that poor and illiterate
                      prisoners can get Legal Advice of their cases.</p></li>
                      <li><p>A good library having books based on literature, religions, autobiography of 
                        renowned persons, etc. is available in the jail and prisoners are making best use of 
                        them.</p></li>
              </ul>
